The paper proposes a technique for learning representations of parser states in transition-based dependency parsers using sequence-to-sequence neural networks. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL. The paper also introduces a new control structure for the neural network, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on parsing could also make it relevant to researchers in computer vision (cs.CV) who are interested in parsing visual scenes.
